The Kabaddi World Cup 2025 is happening across four cities in West Midlands, England; Birmingham, Coventry, Walsall, and Wolverhampton. Ten nations will compete in the men's Kabaddi World Cup 2025, while in the women's World Cup, six teams will be participating. The grand competition began on March 17, 2025, and will end on March 23, 2025. In both the tournaments, India national kabaddi team are the defending champions. The India men's national kabaddi team are clubbed with Italy, Scotland, Wales, and Hong Kong (China) in Group B of the Men‚Äôs Kabaddi World Cup 2025. While the India women's national kabaddi team are clubbed with Wales, and Poland in Group D of the Women‚Äôs Kabaddi World Cup 2025. Matches will be played in Wolverhampton on March 17, March 18, March 22, and March 23. While on March 19, games will be hosted in Coventry, on March 20 in Birmingham, and in Walsall on March 21.
How To Watch Live Telecast of Kabaddi World Cup 2025 on TV in India?
DD Sports has the broadcasting rights in India for the Kabaddi World Cup 2025. Hence, fans can avail of viewing options on the DD Sports TV channel for both men's and women's Kabaddi World Cup 2025 for live telecast. For the live streaming viewing option, read more. How To Watch Live Streaming of Kabaddi World Cup 2025 Online in India?
The live streaming viewing options online of the Kabaddi World Cup 2025 will be available on the Olympics channel website. Fans can access the Olympics.com website and DD Sports to catch the Kabaddi World Cup 2025 live streaming online.

text:
Tonight: Looks like it will be a clear evening as temperatures drift into and through the 50s. Lows range from the upper 30s in the typically colder suburbs to the mid-40s downtown. Very light winds come from the south at 5 mph or less. Confidence: High

Tomorrow (Wednesday): Another winner with mostly sunny skies. Maybe some increasing late-day clouds, and afternoon highs near 70 to the mid-70s. Humidity remains very low. Light winds at 5 to 10 mph from the south, with a few higher gusts possible in the afternoon. Confidence: Medium-High üåû Nice Day!

Tomorrow night: Becoming partly to mostly cloudy and less cool, with lows dropping only to the upper 40s to low 50s. Confidence: High

A look ahead

Thursday contends with an incoming cold front. We could see partial morning sun, then a cloudier afternoon as highs hit the mid-60s to low 70s, west to east. A period of showers and maybe a thunderstorm is possible during the afternoon into evening, with the chance of a brief downpour. Gusty and cooler Thursday night with lows in the upper 30s to low 40s. Confidence: Medium

Friday finds us back in the sunshine, but also with a new cool Canadian air mass in town. Highs stall in the 50s, with blustery winds making it feel like the 40s at times. Friday night looks mostly clear with decreasing winds and lows in the mid-30s to low 40s. Confidence: Medium

Saturday could see a small disturbance kick off a few light showers. Most of the day should be partly sunny and dry, though, with highs warming to the low to mid-60s. Partly cloudy Saturday night as lows dip to the upper 30s to mid-40s. Confidence: Low-Medium

Sunday brings back more sunshine with highs again in the low to mid-60s. Confidence: Medium

Another system has potential to produce a period of rain at some point on Monday with highs near or past 60, then probably cooler highs in the 50s much of next week.

Today‚Äôs daily digit ‚Äî 9/10: Minus one for the morning chill. Otherwise stupendous sunshine and comfortable afternoon warmth earn a stellar score.
title: CWG Live updates Not as cold tonight, then warmer Wednesday; next rain chance Thursday
